The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                  Corporate Briefs

               
	 The Rs 1,100-crore initial public offering of Mumbai-based firm IRB Infrastructure Developers has received approval from market regulator Sebi. The company plans to sell around 5 crore shares of Rs 10 each through the issue, which is expected to hit the market in the third week of January, a company release said. The IPO will be exercised through a 100 per cent book building and will constitute a 15 per cent stake dilution in the company.
              
	 TVS Srichakra Ltd has won the National Energy Conservation award for 2007 in the tyre sector for the large and medium scale industry category. The award recognises industrial units that have made systematic and serious attempts for the efficient utilisation and conservation of energy.
              
	 CARE has assigned CARE AAA rating to Rural Electrification Corporation Ltds borrowing programme aggregating Rs 31,950 crore. The rating agency has also assigned CARE A rating to Andhra Pradesh Power Generation Corporations bonds aggregating Rs 589.8 crore.
              
	 MetricStream has announced its extended offering to support compliance with the Clause 49 requirement laid down by the Securities and Exchange Board of India. MetricStream enables its customers to adopt a single platform for managing multiple GRC initiatives.
              
	 Cummins Turbo Technologies will open a turbocharger manufacturing facility at Pithampur, Madhya Pradesh. Turbo Technologies, the parent company of Cummins Turbo Technologies, is headquartered in Huddersfield, West Yorkshire, England.
              
	 Welspun India has acquired 76 per cent of Portuguese bath rug manufacturer Sorema Tapates e Cortinas de Banho at an enterprise value of Rs 60 crore. The company had also bought an 85 per cent stake in the UK-based towel company Christy in July 2006.
              
	 Gitanjali Group has signed a memorandum of understanding with Italian Mariella Burani Fashion Group. The pact is intended to drive the growth of Mariella Buranis products in India and North America.
              
	 The board of Aegis Logistics Ltd has recommended an interim dividend of 25 per cent, or Rs 2.50 per share. The record date has been fixed on January 9, 2008.
              
	 Suzlon has received an order from ONGC for 52MW wind turbine capacity. The order, which will be supplied in 34 units of Suzlons S82 turbines, will be installed in Kutch, Gujarat.
